title: Investigation of activation cross-sections of proton induced nuclear reactions on natTl up to 42 MeV: Review, new data and evaluation

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Applied Radiation and Isotopes, Vol.74, p.109 (2013)

x4freetext: Experiment 1. Natural Tl 50(micro-m) electroplated onto
brass backing (50 micro-m).
Experiment 2. Natural Tl 15(micro-m) electroplated onto
cupper backing (12.5 micro-m).
Experiment 1. The
irradiation was done at the VUB CGE 560 cyclotron at
beam current of 3-6 microA, for 3-6min. Thirteen
stacks of 7-12 foils were irradiated at incident
energies of 43-22MeV. The number of incident
particles was determined from the integrated charge
measured in Faraday cup. Tl produced in irradiated
samples was quantitatively dissolved after
irradiation and aliquots of 1 ml sample were
measured.
Experiment 2. The irradiation was done at
VUB CGE 560 cyclotron in a short Faraday cup at beam
current 90 nA, for 75 min irradiation time, at 37
MeV incident energy. The radioactivity of the irra-
diated sample and monitor foils was measured
nondestructively using HPGe g-spectrometry. The
nuclear reactions induced on the Cu backing foils
were used as beam monitors.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.240, p.790 (2005)

x4freetext: The uncertainty in energy of each measured
data point was estimated from the uncertainty in
incident beam energy, foil thickness and energy
straggling in the stack.

x4freetext: Quadratic summation of the uncertainties of
the contributing parameters results an absolute error
target thickness (2%)
detector efficiency (5%)
physical decay data (5%)
integrated beam current (2%)
counting statistics (2%)
Fitted excitation functions were used for
determination of integral physical yields.
